d 'KPERRONY': module to determine the number and dates of structural breaks in cointegrated equations, with regime-wise estimates and stability tests 
d
d  kperrony determines the number and dates of structural breaks in
d cointegrated equations (Kejriwal & Perron, 2010; Kejriwal, Perron
d & Yu, 2021). It reports the estimated break dates, regime-wise
d coefficient estimates with HAC standard errors, the
d Kejriwal-Perron-Yu (2021) two-step partial stability test for
d each coefficient, and the Arai-Kurozumi (2007) test of the null
d of cointegration at the estimated breaks, with simulated critical
d values. Serially correlated errors are handled through the robust
d versions of the tests, and endogenous I(1) regressors through the
d dynamic OLS leads and lags, both added automatically. Critical
d values are embedded for up to five breaks with 15 percent
d trimming. 
d
d KW: unit root tests
d KW: cointegration
d KW: structural breaks
d
d Requires: Stata version 14
d
d Distribution-Date: 20260718
d
d Author: Ozan Eruygur,  Ankara Haci Bayram Veli University
d Support: email eruygur@@gmail.com
